      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey can u explain what actually happens in my muscles when i do hiit? specifically like how does lactic acid actually get produced and how does my body get rid of it after the workout?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "During HIIT, your muscles are working so hard that they start to produce energy faster than oxygen can be supplied, leading to a process that creates lactic acid. This is a byproduct of anaerobic respiration, which is your body's way of making quick energy when the oxygen supply is limited. After the workout, your body uses processes like the Cori cycle and oxidative metabolism to convert some of that lactate back into glucose or use it as fuel, helping to clear it out.",
      "source": "target",
